				<td colspan="2"><span>He might be using the /target name trick.  I do this when I'm AoE kiting so I can see how much health the mobs have.  It targets the mob closest to you with the name you specified.  I change my macro depending on where I am kiting, but he could well be using a single macro with a bunch of /target to get any mob around him ... 
<br />

<br />
I have seen programs like MMOGer that could be used to setup a simple macro to do this.  I would report report him.  Would be funny to kill him and then see him running circles in PoK around the soulbinder <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
