			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Using script, dot kite, and went AFK. legal?<a name="34833"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 15 04 1:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This is one of the simplier Macros.
<br />

<br />
The good ones will run to the camp spot, go pull mobs to kite, chant them all down (it wont target friendly mobs or NPCs) and when the mobs are dead it goes and rounds up more.
<br />

<br />
These super macros even check to see if another player is within viewable distance of you. If they are it will move you away. If people keep comming into range of you, or if a GM logs on, it will run you to the zoneline, click on the portal and camp you out.
<br />

<br />
I know, because I was interested in how powerful these were and decided to really investigate the macroing forums. I would highly suggest that nobody tries using of these macros. While they seem like miracles at first, if you do get caught (and you can get caught, its just harder with the good ones) you will be banned.
<br />

<br />
AFK auto leveling like this is looked upon very harshly by Sony. The only type of macroing Sony allows is attended macros, especially for people with a physical disability. At the fan faire Ryatn said flat out you could use a macro to twist if you had a disability and were physically at the computer while it was happening.
<br />

<br />
So yes, these things are possible. But no, I won't tell you where to get them, and if you do get your hands on one don't use it unless you like getting your account banned.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
