				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Using script, dot kite, and went AFK. legal?<a name="35652"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 20 04 6:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Exactly Stefenn. This whole post is about macros (scripts) that do this for you. And we have concluded that they are not legal unless you are at your computer. And you could just have your macro use F8 a couple times every 5-10 minutes for complete AFKness. However, other variables come in to play and you do risk death and/or being caught, leading to a ban most likely. 
<br />

<br />
I can twist four chants with an n52 macro, but I wouldn't autorun and go afk. What if a wanderer pops a stun on you? Lag happens also. I might autorun and macro twist, but I wouldn't leave the computer for long at all. </span></td>
