				<td colspan="2"><span>also of note to this is that his circles were in all likelyhood not actually perfect.  I have been told many times when i kite that my circles are perfect but from my view point they are way off.  i tend to find something on the ground to follow, such as floor tiles, marks in the sand, whatever and i just stick to it as best i can, from the overhead / behind view i can tell that i am off, but when watching another bard from first person it does look like they are doing perfect circles.  i also have kited for greater than 9 hours strait and though it is hard and does cause cramps i  take great pride in the fact that i can do this even when people tell me that soe nerffed such and such a zone and that ae kiting can no longer be done there.  loot is really up for grabs, when i kite i do it for the loot, i only kite in areas where tradeskill drops will fall, the xp is just an added bonus.  now i will not say that i have not kited for the xp, but the places i normally kite now are a good combination of both.  while i know that many bards do use scripts or third party macros it is possible to do what you have described without using a macro or script just that the person has to have great skill to do such.  maybe he is like me and likes to be able to say that he can do it, maybe he wants to show off, maybe he is trying to prove that he is not using a script, i myself have welcomed a gm and the rest of the zone to come and watch my kite so i could prove to some that have questioned my abilities.  Now if he is using a script or third party macro and is not at keyboard sure he should be trained and banned but if it is skill then appalaud him, just be certain of what it is first before taking action. </span></td>
