				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Using script, dot kite, and went AFK. legal?<a name="39947"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 14 04 9:40 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Agreed, but at 65 with epic you should still be able to run in a big enough circle to avoid being hit. Also try pressing enter twice and releasing the forward and right keys. This will give you a slightly larger circle then just forward and right does. Aside from how fast you are running, what you are kiting has the largest impact on how big your circle has to be. A giant is impossible to kite this way, but humans and hoppers are a piece of very moist cake.
<br />

<br />
As far as the script thing goes, would I be unethical to use one to twist songs on my bard while I played another character 2-boxing or even grouped? I find the biggest reason I cannot get full use of my bard's abilities when boxing is I simply cannot keep a good twist going while i reach over and hit buttons on the other keyboard.</span></td>
